Description: Periodic maintenance daemon for MultiFlexi
 MultiFlexi HouseKeeper performs housekeeping duties to keep the
 MultiFlexi platform running flawlessly. It runs on an hourly systemd
 timer and executes the following duties in order:
 .
  * Stale task finalization — marks expired open/running tasks as missed
    or failed so the obligation metric stays accurate
  * Orphaned job cleanup — removes jobs with broken company/runtemplate
    references and ghost queue entries
  * Schedule integrity — resets stale next_schedule values so the
    scheduler daemon re-picks stuck runtemplates
  * Data retention cleanup — enforces GDPR retention policies, hard- or
    soft-deleting expired rows from job, log, user_sessions, and other
    tables (uses RetentionService when multiflexi-web is installed)
  * Disk temp file cleanup — removes orphaned result files left behind
    after artifact storage
  * Log pruning — keeps the log table below a configurable row count
  * RunTemplate counter recalculation — corrects drifted success/failure
    job counters after retention deletions
  * Credential health check — calls checkAvailability() on credentials
    assigned to active runtemplates; reports Misconfigured credentials
    before they block a job at runtime
 .
 Runs as a systemd timer (hourly) or as a long-running daemon when
 MULTIFLEXI_DAEMONIZE=true. Supports a --dry-run mode for safe previews.
